#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:8
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting up a UEFI HTTP Boot Server"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:11
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter describes how to set up and configure a UEFI HTTP Boot server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:21
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:23
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"HTTP Boot combines DHCP, DNS, and HTTP to make it possible to boot and "
"deploy systems over the network. HTTP Boot can be used as a high-performance "
"replacement for PXE. HTTP Boot allows to boot a server from a URI over HTTP, "
"quickly transferring large files, such as the Linux kernel and root file "
"system from servers outside of your local network."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:32
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring the Client Machine"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:33
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enabling HTTP Boot on a physical client machine depends on your specific "
"hardware. Consult the documentation for further information on how to enable "
"HTTP Boot on your particular machine."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:41
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preparation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:42
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The setup described here uses 192.168.111.0/24 (IPv4) and 2001:db8:f00f:"
"cafe::/64 (IPv6) IP subnets and the server IP addresses are "
"192.168.111.1(IPv4) and 2001:db8:f00f:cafe::1/64 (IPv6) as examples. Adjust "
"these values to match your specific setup."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:48
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Install the following packages on the machine that you plan to use as a HTTP "
"Boot server: <package>dhcp-server</package> , <package>apache2</package> (or "
"<package>lighttpd</package> ), and <package>dnsmasq</package> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring the Server"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:60
#, no-c-format
msgid "DNS Server"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:61
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"While configuring the DNS server is optional, this does allow you to assign "
"a user-friendly name to the HTTP Boot server. To set up the DNS server, add "
"the following to the <filename>/etc/dnsmasq.conf</filename> file:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:66
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"interface=eth0\n"
"addn-hosts=/etc/dnsmasq.d/hosts.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:68
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Assign a domain name to the IP addresses in the <filename>/etc/dnsmasq.d/"
"hosts.conf</filename> file:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:72
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"192.168.111.1 www.httpboot.local\n"
"2001:db8:f00f:cafe::1 www.httpboot.local"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start the DNS server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "systemctl start dnsmasq"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:79
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Due to the change in UEFI 2.7, we recommend using a shim bootloader from "
"&slea; 15 or newer to avoid potential errors caused by the additional DNS "
"node."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring the DHCPv4 Server"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:87
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before setting up the DHCP servers, specify the network interface for them "
"in <filename>/etc/sysconfig/dhcpd</filename> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:91
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"DHCPD_INTERFACE=\"eth0\"\n"
"DHCPD6_INTERFACE=\"eth0\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:93
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This way, the DHCP servers provide the service on the <literal>eth0</"
"literal> interface only."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:97
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To set up a DHCPv4 server for both PXE Boot and HTTP Boot, add the following "
"configuration to the <filename>/etc/dhcpd.conf</filename> file:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:101
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"option domain-name-servers 192.168.111.1;\n"
"option routers 192.168.111.1;\n"
"default-lease-time 14400;\n"
"ddns-update-style none;\n"
"  subnet 192.168.111.0 netmask 255.255.255.0 {\n"
"    range dynamic-bootp 192.168.111.100 192.168.111.120;\n"
"    default-lease-time 14400;\n"
"    max-lease-time 172800;\n"
"    class \"pxeclients\"{\n"
"      match if substring (option vendor-class-identifier, 0, 9) = \"PXEClient"
"\";\n"
"      next-server 192.168.111.1;\n"
"      filename \"/bootx64.efi\";\n"
"    }\n"
"    class \"httpclients\" {\n"
"      match if substring (option vendor-class-identifier, 0, 10) = "
"\"HTTPClient\";\n"
"      option vendor-class-identifier \"HTTPClient\";\n"
"      filename \"http://www.httpboot.local/sle/EFI/BOOT/bootx64.efi\";\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:120
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that the DHCPv4 server must use the <literal>HTTPClient</literal> "
"parameter for the vendor class ID, as the client uses it to identify an HTTP "
"Boot offer."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:125
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start the DHCP daemon:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:128
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>systemctl start dhcpd</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:133
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring the DHCPv6 Server"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:134
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To set up the DHCPv6 server, add the following configuration to <filename>/"
"etc/dhcpd6.conf</filename> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:138
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"option dhcp6.bootfile-url code 59 = string;\n"
"option dhcp6.vendor-class code 16 = {integer 32, integer 16, string};\n"
"subnet6 2001:db8:f00f:cafe::/64 {\n"
"        range6 2001:db8:f00f:cafe::42:10 2001:db8:f00f:cafe::42:99;\n"
"        option dhcp6.bootfile-url \"http://www.httpboot.local/sle/EFI/BOOT/"
"bootx64.efi\";\n"
"        option dhcp6.name-servers 2001:db8:f00f:cafe::1;\n"
"        option dhcp6.vendor-class 0 10 \"HTTPClient\";\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:146
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This configuration defines the type of the boot URL, the vendor class, and "
"other required options. Similar to the DHCPv4 settings, it is necessary to "
"provide the boot URL, which must have an IPv6 address. It is also necessary "
"to specify the vendor class option. In DHCPv6, it consists of the enterprise "
"number and the vendor class data (length and the content). Since the HTTP "
"Boot driver ignores the enterprise number, you can set it to <literal>0</"
"literal> . The content of the vendor class data has to be "
"<literal>HTTPClient</literal> ; Otherwise, the client ignores the offer."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:156
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The older HTTP Boot implementation, which does not follow <link xlink:href="
"\"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3315\">RFC 3315</link> , requires a "
"different configuration:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:161
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"option dhcp6.bootfile-url code 59 = string;\n"
"option dhcp6.vendor-class code 16 = string;\n"
"        subnet6 2001:db8:f00f:cafe::/64 {\n"
"        range6 2001:db8:f00f:cafe::42:10 2001:db8:f00f:cafe::42:99;\n"
"        option dhcp6.bootfile-url \"http://www.httpboot.local/sle/EFI/BOOT/"
"bootx64.efi;\n"
"\toption dhcp6.name-servers 2001:db8:f00f:cafe::1;\n"
"\toption dhcp6.vendor-class \"HTTPClient\";\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:169
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start the <literal>dhcpv6</literal> daemon."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:172
#, no-c-format
msgid "systemctl start dhcpd6"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:174
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting up the DHCPv6 Server for Both PXE and HTTP Boot"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:175
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using the following configuration, it is possible to configure the DHCPv6 "
"server for both PXE Boot and HTTP Boot:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:179
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"option dhcp6.bootfile-url code 59 = string;\n"
"option dhcp6.vendor-class code 16 = {integer 32, integer 16, string};\n"
"\n"
"subnet6 2001:db8:f00f:cafe::/64 {\n"
"        range6 2001:db8:f00f:cafe::42:10 2001:db8:f00f:cafe::42:99;\n"
"\n"
"        class \"PXEClient\" {\n"
"\t        match substring (option dhcp6.vendor-class, 6, 9);\n"
"\t}\n"
"\n"
"        subclass \"PXEClient\" \"PXEClient\" {\n"
"\t        option dhcp6.bootfile-url \"tftp://[2001:db8:f00f:cafe::1]/"
"bootloader.efi\";\n"
"\t}\n"
"\n"
"\tclass \"HTTPClient\"; {\n"
"\t        match substring (option dhcp6.vendor-class, 6, 10);\n"
"\t}\n"
"\n"
"\tsubclass \"HTTPClient\" \"HTTPClient\" {\n"
"\t        option dhcp6.bootfile-url \"http://www.httpboot.local/sle/EFI/BOOT/"
"bootx64.efi\";\n"
"\t\toption dhcp6.name-servers 2001:db8:f00f:cafe::1;\n"
"\t\toption dhcp6.vendor-class 0 10 \"HTTPClient\";\n"
"\t}\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:203
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is also possible to match the vendor class to a specific architecture, as "
"follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:207
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"class \"HTTPClient\" {\n"
"        match substring (option dhcp6.vendor-class, 6, 21);\n"
"\t}\n"
"\n"
"subclass \"HTTPClient\" \"HTTPClient\":Arch:00016 {\n"
"        option dhcp6.bootfile-url \"http://www.httpboot.local/sle/EFI/BOOT/"
"bootx64.efi\";\n"
"\toption dhcp6.name-servers 2001:db8:f00f:cafe::1;\n"
"\toption dhcp6.vendor-class 0 10 \"HTTPClient\";\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:216
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this example, <literal>HTTPClient:Arch:00016</literal> refers to a x86_64 "
"HTTP Boot client. This configuration allows the server to serve different "
"architectures simultaneously."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:223
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring Firewall"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:224
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If DHCPv6 packets are dropped by the RP filter in the firewall, check its "
"log. In case it contains the <literal>rpfilter_DROP</literal> entry, disable "
"the filter using the following configuration in <filename>/etc/firewalld/"
"firewalld.conf</filename> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:230
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>IPv6_rpfilter=no</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:236
#, no-c-format
msgid "Deploying a TFTP server (Optional)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:237
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To provide support for both PXE Boot and HTTP Boot, deploy a TFTP server. "
"Install the <package>tftp</package> and start the service:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:241
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
" systemctl start tftp.socket\n"
"systemctl start tftp.service"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:243
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is also necessary to install a specific <package>tftpboot-installation</"
"package> package for use with PXE Boot. Run the <command>zypper se tftpboot</"
"command> command, to list of the available <package>tftp-installation</"
"package> packages, then install the package for the desired system version "
"and architecture, for example <package>tftpboot-installation-SLE-15-SP2-"
"x86_64</package> For example, <package os=\"osuse\">tftpboot-installation-"
"openSUSE-<replaceable>VERSION</replaceable>-x86_64</package> <package os="
"\"sles;sled\">tftpboot-installation-SLE-<replaceable>VERSION</replaceable>-"
"x86_64</package> (replace <replaceable>VERSION</replaceable> with the actual "
"version). Copy the content of the <filename os=\"osuse\">openSUSE-"
"<replaceable>VERSION</replaceable>-x86_64</filename> <filename os=\"sles;sled"
"\">SLE-<replaceable>VERSION</replaceable>-x86_64</filename> directory to the "
"root directory of the TFTP server:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:260
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"cp -r /usr/share/tftpboot-installation/openSUSE-<replaceable>VERSION</"
"replaceable>-x86_64 /srv/tftpboot"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:261
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"cp -r /usr/share/tftpboot-installation/SLE-<replaceable>VERSION</"
"replaceable>-x86_64 /srv/tftpboot"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:262
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For more information, refer to <filename os=\"osuse\">/usr/share/tftpboot-"
"installation/openSUSE-<replaceable>VERSION</replaceable>-x86_64/README</"
"filename> <filename os=\"sles;sled\">/usr/share/tftpboot-installation/SLE-"
"<replaceable>VERSION</replaceable>-x86_64/README</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:270
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting up the HTTP Server"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:271
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Copy the entire content of the first system ISO image to the <filename os="
"\"osuse\">/srv/www/htdocs/opensuse/</filename> <filename os=\"sles;sled\">/"
"srv/www/htdocs/sle/</filename> directory. Edit then the <filename os=\"osuse"
"\">/srv/www/htdocs/opensuse/grub.cfg</filename> <filename os=\"sles;sled\">/"
"srv/www/htdocs/sle/grub.cfg</filename> file. Use the following example as a "
"reference:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:282
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"timeout=60\n"
"default=1\n"
"\n"
"menuentry 'Installation IPv4' --class opensuse --class gnu-linux --class gnu "
"--class os {\n"
"    set gfxpayload=keep\n"
"    echo 'Loading kernel ...'\n"
"    linuxefi /sle/boot/x86_64/loader/linux install=http://www.httpboot.local/"
"sle\n"
"    echo 'Loading initial ramdisk ...'\n"
"    initrdefi /sle/boot/x86_64/loader/initrd\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"menuentry 'Installation IPv6' --class opensuse --class gnu-linux --class gnu "
"--class os {\n"
"    set gfxpayload=keep\n"
"    echo 'Loading kernel ...'\n"
"    linuxefi /sle/boot/x86_64/loader/linux install=install=http://www."
"httpboot.local/sle ipv6only=1 ifcfg=*=dhcp6,DHCLIENT6_MODE=managed\n"
"    echo 'Loading initial ramdisk ...'\n"
"    initrdefi /sle/boot/x86_64/loader/initrd\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:301
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring lighttpd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:302
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To enable the support for both IPv4 and IPv6 in lighttpd, modify <filename>/"
"etc/lighttpd/lighttpd.conf</filename> as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:306
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"##\n"
"## Use IPv6?\n"
"##\n"
"#server.use-ipv6 = \"enable\"\n"
"$SERVER[\"socket\"] == \"[::]:80\" {  }"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:311
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start the <literal>lighttpd</literal> daemon:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:314
#, no-c-format
msgid "systemctl start lighttpd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:317
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring apache2"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:318
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Apache requires no additional configuration. Start the <literal>apache2</"
"literal> daemon:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:322
#, no-c-format
msgid "systemctl start apache2"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:326
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling SSL Support for the HTTP Server (Optional)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:327
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use the HTTPS Boot, you need to convert an existing server certificate "
"into the <literal>DER</literal> format and enroll it into the client's "
"firmware."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:332
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Assuming you already have a certificate installed on your server, convert it "
"into the <literal>DER</literal> format for use with the client using the "
"following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:337
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"openssl x509 -in <replaceable>CERTIFICATE</replaceable>.crt -outform der -"
"out <replaceable>CERTIFICATE</replaceable>.der"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:339
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enroll The Server Certificate into the Client Firmware"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:340
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The exact procedure of enrolling the converted certificate depends on the "
"specific implementation of the client's firmware. For certain hardware, you "
"have to enroll the certificate manually via the firmware UI using an "
"external storage device with the certificate on it. Machines with Redfish "
"support can enroll the certificate remotely. Consult documentation for your "
"specific hardware for more information on enrolling certificates."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:350
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling SSL Support in lighttpd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:351
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since lighttpd needs the private key and the certificate in the same file, "
"unify them using the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:355
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"cat <replaceable>CERTIFICATE</replaceable>.crt server.key &gt; "
"<replaceable>CERTIFICATE</replaceable>.pem"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:356
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Copy <filename><replaceable>CERTIFICATE</replaceable>.pem</filename> to the "
"<filename>/etc/ssl/private/</filename> directory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:360
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"cp server-almighty.pem /etc/ssl/private/\n"
"chown -R root:lighttpd /etc/ssl/private/server-almighty.pem\n"
"chmod 640 /etc/ssl/private/server-almighty.pem"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:363
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure that <literal>mod_openssl</literal> is listed in the "
"<literal>server.modules</literal> section of the <filename>/etc/lighttpd/"
"modules.conf</filename> file, for example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:368
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"server.modules = (\n"
"  \"mod_access\",\n"
"  \"mod_openssl\",\n"
")"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:372
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Add the following lines to <literal>SSL Support</literal> section in "
"<filename>/etc/lighttpd/lighttpd.conf</filename> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:376
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"# IPv4\n"
"$SERVER[\"socket\"] == \":443\" {\n"
"    ssl.engine                 = \"enable\"\n"
"    ssl.pemfile                = \"/etc/ssl/private/server-almighty.pem\"\n"
"}\n"
"# IPv6\n"
"$SERVER[\"socket\"] == \"[::]:443\" {\n"
"    ssl.engine                 = \"enable\"\n"
"    ssl.pemfile                = \"/etc/ssl/private/server-almighty.pem\"\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:386
#, no-c-format
msgid "Restart lighttpd to activate SSL support:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:389
#, no-c-format
msgid "systemctl restart lighttpd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:392
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling SSL Support in Apache"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:393
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open the <filename>/etc/sysconfig/apache2</filename> file and add the SSL "
"flag as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:397
#, no-c-format
msgid "APACHE_SERVER_FLAGS=\"SSL\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:398
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure that the <literal>ssl</literal> module is listed in "
"<literal>APACHE_MODULES</literal> , for example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:402
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Next, copy the private key and the certificate to the <filename>/etc/apache2/"
"</filename> directory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:406
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"cp server.key /etc/apache2/ssl.key/\n"
"chown wwwrun /etc/apache2/ssl.key/server.key\n"
"chmod 600 /etc/apache2/ssl.key/server.key\n"
"cp server.crt /etc/apache2/ssl.crt/"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:410
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create the ssl vhost configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:413
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"cd /etc/apache2/vhosts.d\n"
"cp vhost-ssl.template vhost-ssl.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:415
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Edit <filename>/etc/apache2/vhosts.d/vhost-ssl.conf</filename> to change the "
"private key and the certificate:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:419
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SSLCertificateFile /etc/apache2/ssl.crt/server.crt\n"
" SSLCertificateKeyFile /etc/apache2/ssl.key/server.key"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:421
#, no-c-format
msgid "Restart apache to activate the SSL support:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:424
#, no-c-format
msgid "systemctl restart apache2"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:427
#, no-c-format
msgid "Modify the DHCP configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:428
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Replace the <literal>http://</literal> prefix with <literal>https://</"
"literal> in <filename>dhcpd.conf/dhcpd6.conf</filename> and restart the dhcp "
"server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: uefi-httpboot-server.xml:433
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"systemctl restart dhcpd\n"
"systemctl restart dhcpd6"
msgstr ""

